Make Runnable decorator that catches, remembers and rethrows the 
Assertion Failure ?


Off the top of my head .....


public void testSomething() {
   // set up stuff

   RunnableAssertion runnable =
       new RunnableAssertion(new RealRunnable());
   Thread thread = new Thread(runnable);
   thread.start();
   thread.join();

   runnable.rethrowExceptions();

   // more assertions
}

public class RunnableAssertion implements Runnable {
   Runnable realRunnable;
   Throwable exception;

   public RunnableAssertion(Runnable runnable) {
     this.realRunnable = realRunnable;
   }

   public void run() {
     try {
       realRunnable.run();
     }
     catch(Throwable t){
       this.exception = t;
     }
   }

   public void reThrowExceptions() throws Throwable {
     if(exception != null){
       throw exception;
     }
   }
}


But I would try to avoid relying on the thread in the test :-)


